Shehu Sani, a former federal lawmaker and activist, has revealed the exact words of former President Olusegun Obasanjo when both men were sentenced to life imprisonment in 1995.  Recall that Obasanjo was arrested and convicted of being part of a planned coup in 1995, having been openly critical of the government of military dictator, Sani Abacha.He was imprisoned despite protesting his innocence and there in the prison, Obasanjo was said to have become a born again Christian.Also, Sani, a human rights activist was arrested and jailed by successive past military regimes.Sani found luck and was released from life imprisonment when democracy was restored in Nigeria in 1999.He went ahead to contest the Kaduna Central Senatorial District which he won on the platform of the All Progressive Congress on 28 March 2015Recalling his days with the former military head of state who turned 85 years last week, Sani tweeted, “When the Military Tribunal Judge in Lagos sentenced Obj to life imprisonment for treason and sentenced me and Dr Beko to life imprisonment plus 7 years for treason, Obj turned to me and asked ‘young man, which one are you going to start with, the 7 years or the life imprisonment?’”Sani recalled yesterday that when they were in Kiri Kiri prison together, no prisoner wanted to serve Obasanjo because he hardly remains food for the boys who washed their dishes.  Source A former president, Olusegun Obasanjo, has narrated how he was almost rescued from prison The former president said some of his 'international friends' planned to rescue him in a helicopter He said he however rejected their offer and told them he would not leave the prison A former president of… In "Top Stories" Local Government Autonomy: Shehu Shows Solidarity With NULGE Protesters In "Top Stories" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Late General Victor Malu was the Chairman of the seven-man Special Military Tribunal (SMT), that tried General Oladipo Diya for alleged coup plot against the administration of Gen